Batch Restore allows you to restore all:
Batch Restore allows you to restore all savedata from a BatchBackup 
* to the same user profiles
* to a different user in the same console 
* or to a different console where the games are already installed.
In the later case, it is recommended to first run the game to 
  initialize the savedata.
Batch Wipe allows you to wipe savedata b:
Batch Wipe allows you to wipe savedata belonging to a given profile
across all selected titles.
It detects also savedata belonging to profiles not defined in the console.

Just:
- select which data to wipe
- select titles to act on
- and go!
